  "text": "For the third round of experiments, we tested a series of popular object recognition algorithms that can be used for digital image forensics applications using the machine learning-based meta-recognition algorithm. In this case, we have considered standard SIFT [CITATION_1] with all features except DCT, which did not yield results better than random chance for our data. For the content-based image retrieval experiments, we considered simple local color histograms. All features except for were utilized for CBIR. The results of Fig. 7 show a significant increase in accuracy for the fusion techniques.",
